qas.question: During what period did Tito pursue a policy of neutrality?
With whom did Tito's belief in self-determination cause a rift?
What type of countries did Tito develop relations with?
Who had a strong belief in self-determination and was opposed to Stalin because of this?
Tito had cordial relations with the United States and what other Western area?

context: <a3_0>Tito<a3_0/> was notable for pursuing a foreign policy of neutrality during the <a0_0>Cold War<a0_0/> and for establishing close ties with <a2_0>developing<a2_0/> countries. Tito's strong belief in self-determination caused early rift with <a1_0>Stalin<a1_0/> and consequently, the Eastern Bloc. His public speeches often reiterated that policy of neutrality and cooperation with all countries would be natural as long as these countries did not use their influence to pressure Yugoslavia to take sides. Relations with the United States and <a4_0>Western European nations<a4_0/> were generally cordial.
